      "source_audio": "../vox-chsh-arithmetic/mp3/beat-B01.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B02",
      "t_start": 10.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 12.0,
      "narration_text": "If hidden instructions govern the outcomes — if each particle carries pre-assigned values — then S cannot exceed 2. That is the classical bound. Quantum mechanics predicts two root two, about 2.83. Experiments confirm the quantum prediction.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "new_visual_element": "[SCALE] S axis with classical bound at 2 and quantum at 2root2",
      "audio_file": "../vox-chsh-arithmetic/mp3/beat-B02.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 16.2,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-chsh-arithmetic/clips/B02.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-chsh-arithmetic/mp3/beat-B02.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B03",
      "t_start": 22.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10.0,
      "narration_text": "Local realism and quantum mechanics predict different numbers for S. The classical bound of 2 should follow from deep physics. But it drops out of a four-row table a third-grader could check. Why?",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold",
        "remotion": {
          "pattern": "SlateCard",
          "provenance": "proven-core/SlateCard",
          "version": "1",
          "props": {
            "headline": "Local realism and quantum mechanics predict different numbers for S. The…",
            "eyebrow": "",
            "topic": ""
          }
        }
      },
      "card": {
        "kind": "dek",
        "copy": "Why does the classical bound of 2\nfall out of a four-row table?",
        "sub": "THE QUESTION"
      },
      "new_visual_element": "[QUESTION] why arithmetic gives the bound",
      "audio_file": "../vox-chsh-arithmetic/mp3/beat-B03.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 12.15,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-chsh-arithmetic/clips/B03.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-chsh-arithmetic/mp3/beat-B03.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "t_start": 32.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 12.0,
      "narration_text": "Under local realism, each particle carries a pre-assigned answer for every setting. Alice's answer for setting A1 is plus one or minus one. Same for A2. Bob has B1 and B2. One instruction set lambda assigns definite values to all four.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "new_visual_element": "[DIAGRAM] lambda assigns A1,A2,B1,B2 values each +1/-1",
      "audio_file": "../vox-chsh-arithmetic/mp3/beat-B04.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 16.61,
      "locked": true,
