    {
      "beat_id": "B11",
      "t_start": 98.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 12.0,
      "narration_text": "S is bounded by 2 for every possible hidden-variable assignment — not on average, but always, for each lambda. Averaging over all assignments can only keep S at most 2. The bound is a theorem about arithmetic on plus-one and minus-one numbers, not a theorem about physics.",
