    {
      "beat_id": "B13",
      "t_start": 115.0,
      "estimated_duration_s": 12.0,
      "narration_text": "Quantum mechanics predicts S up to two root two, about 2.83. That is 41 percent above the classical bound. Experiments confirm it. So quantum outcomes are not pre-assigned plus-one minus-one numbers — at least not in any locally realistic way.",
      "shot": {
